        id: "learning-pathways--t3-02-adjustment-frameworks",
        title: "Adjustment Frameworks",
        description: "By the end of this module, you will have a working understanding of this topic and be able to apply it in your management practice.",
        content: "# Adjustment Frameworks\n\n## Learning objectives\n\nBy the end of this module, you will have a working understanding of this topic and be able to apply it in your management practice.\n\n## Core content\n\nA structured approach to identifying, implementing, and reviewing workplace adjustments. Step 1: Identify the barrier. Step 2: Explore solutions together. Step 3: Agree and document. Step 4: Implement promptly. Step 5: Review regularly. Most adjustments are low cost or free: written instructions, flexible timing, environmental changes, communication preferences. The conversation should feel collaborative, not clinical. Document what is agreed. Act quickly. Review periodically. If a specific adjustment is not possible, work together on alternatives.\n\n## Reflection questions\n\n1. How does this topic apply to your current team?\n2. What is one change you could make based on this module?\n3. What support do you need to implement this effectively?\n\n## Further resources\n\nRefer to the Manager Toolkit for practical guides and templates related to this topic.\n",
