        id: "learning-library--13-leader",
        title: "Leader",
        description: "Neuroinclusive leadership means embedding neurodiversity into organisational strategy, not just delegating it to HR or a champion programme. Leaders set the tone. When leaders visibly prioritise ne...",
        content: "# Leader\n\nNeuroinclusive leadership means embedding neurodiversity into organisational strategy, not just delegating it to HR or a champion programme. Leaders set the tone. When leaders visibly prioritise neuroinclusion, allocate resources, and hold themselves accountable, the organisation follows. Key leadership actions: name a senior neuroinclusion sponsor, include neurodiversity in the D&I strategy, allocate budget, measure progress, and listen to neurodivergent employees. The business case is strong: neurodiverse teams are more innovative, more productive, and more resilient.\n\n## Further reading\n\nExplore the related guides and modules in the toolkit for practical applications of this topic.\n",
