        id: "learning-library--15-policy",
        title: "Policy",
        description: "Neuroinclusion needs to be reflected in organisational policy to be sustainable. Key policy areas: the D&I strategy should explicitly reference neurodivergence, the reasonable adjustments policy sh...",
        content: "# Policy\n\nNeuroinclusion needs to be reflected in organisational policy to be sustainable. Key policy areas: the D&I strategy should explicitly reference neurodivergence, the reasonable adjustments policy should be clear and accessible, recruitment and performance management policies should be reviewed for neuroinclusive practice, and communication standards should account for different processing styles. Policies should be written in plain language, reviewed regularly, and developed with input from neurodivergent employees.\n\n## Further reading\n\nExplore the related guides and modules in the toolkit for practical applications of this topic.\n",
