        content: "# Manager\n\nManagers are the single most important factor in whether neuroinclusion works in practice. Key management capabilities for neuroinclusion: responding well to disclosure, having adjustment conversations, communicating clearly and specifically, distinguishing between performance issues and support needs, creating psychological safety, and sustaining inclusive practice over time. Managers do not need to be experts in neurodivergence. They need to be willing to listen, adapt, and act.\n\n## Further reading\n\nExplore the related guides and modules in the toolkit for practical applications of this topic.\n",
