        id: "microlearning--01-managing-energy-not-just-time",
        title: "Managing Energy, Not Just Time",
        description: "Time management assumes consistent energy. For neurodivergent people, energy fluctuates significantly throughout the day. The key shift: instead of asking 'When is this due?' ask 'When do I have th...",
        content: "# Managing Energy, Not Just Time\n\n## Microlearning Module\n\nTime management assumes consistent energy. For neurodivergent people, energy fluctuates significantly throughout the day. The key shift: instead of asking 'When is this due?' ask 'When do I have the energy to do this well?' Map your energy peaks and dips over a few days. Schedule demanding tasks during peaks. Use dips for routine or low demand work. Build in recovery between high cost activities (meetings, social interaction, sensory environments). Protect your peak time fiercely. Energy management is not about doing less. It is about doing the right things at the right times.\n\n## Key takeaway\n\nApply one thing from this module today.\n",
