        content: "# When Someone Discloses What to Say\n\n## Quick Reference\n\nWhen someone discloses a neurodivergent condition: 1. Listen. Do not interrupt. 2. Say: 'Thank you for telling me. I appreciate you trusting me with this.' 3. Ask: 'How can I support you at work?' 4. Do not ask about their diagnosis, medical history, or how they 'got it.' 5. Follow up in writing with agreed next steps. 6. Keep it completely confidential unless they give permission. 7. Implement what you agreed. Do not let the conversation lead to nothing.\n",
