        content: "# Adjustment Conversation Framework\n\n## Quick Reference\n\nStep 1: Start with an open question. 'Is there anything about how we're set up that makes your work harder than it needs to be?' Step 2: Listen for specifics. What is the barrier? What would help? Step 3: Be specific in what you can offer. 'I can arrange X by Y.' Step 4: Explore alternatives if the first option is not possible. Step 5: Document what you agree: what the adjustment is, who implements it, when it starts, when you review. Step 6: Act quickly. Step 7: Check in after two weeks.\n",
