        content: "# Return After Overwhelm Manager Guide\n\n## Quick Reference\n\nAfter someone has experienced overwhelm: do not expect an immediate return to normal, offer a phased re engagement (start with familiar low demand tasks), check in privately and briefly, watch for overcompensation (pushing too hard to prove they are fine), ask what contributed to the overwhelm and what could prevent it next time. The goal is recovery and prevention, not just resuming output.\n",
