        content: "# Escalation Pathway\n\n## Quick Reference\n\nLevel 1 (Manager): Day to day adjustments, communication, check ins, initial support. Level 2 (HR): Formal adjustment requests, policy questions, performance management, grievances, occupational health referrals. Level 3 (Occupational Health): Professional assessment, adjustment recommendations, return to work plans. Level 4 (External): Access to Work funding, ACAS advice, specialist coaching, trade union support. Always involve the employee in escalation decisions. Frame it as better support, not a problem being passed on.\n",
