        content: "# Rota Flexibility Guide\n\n## Quick Reference\n\nScheduling flexibility options: flexible start and finish times, consistent patterns where possible, advance notice of schedule changes (as much lead time as you can give), written communication of all changes, protected focused work periods, adjusted break patterns to match energy needs, avoidance of back to back demanding periods. The goal is predictability and control. Not rigidity, but structure that supports rather than restricts.\n",
