        content: "# Video Script: Neuroinclusion: Simple Tools\n\n## Production brief\n\nA short introduction to practical neuroinclusion tools anyone can use. Cover: what neuroinclusion means in one sentence, three things anyone can do today (share meeting agendas, ask how someone prefers to receive information, normalise breaks), why small changes matter. Tone: warm, practical, encouraging. Duration target: 2 to 3 minutes. Visual: real workplace settings, diverse cast, text overlays for key points.\n\n## Script outline\n\n### Opening (15 to 30 seconds)\nHook the viewer with a relatable moment or question.\n\n### Core content (main body)\nDeliver the key messages using a mix of narration, on screen text, and visual examples.\n\n### Closing (15 to 30 seconds)\nSummarise the one key takeaway. Direct the viewer to related resources on the platform.\n\n## Accessibility requirements\n\nCaptions on all video content.\nAudio description available.\nTranscript provided alongside the video.\nClear, plain language throughout.\nVisuals support the audio content (not decorative only).\n",
